event.title: the early 1900s, a railway was built

data.event: In the early 1900s, a railway was built, passing through the town on its route between Starke and Wannee.
A train depot was built around 1905, and the restored depot building is now the Town Hall.
On September 18, 2014, a man, identified as 51-year-old ex-convict Don Charles Spirit, shot dead his daughter Sarah and her six children.
